In Singapore with its 78% of all the population vaccinated (kids included) strict border measures and aggressive testing and tracing have helped keep a lid on cases, as well as two very different sets of rules for the vaccinated and unvaccinated. Is @ScottMorrisonMP up to that?

@MichaelSFuhrer @RichardfromSyd1 @KrispyOz31 @BrentHodgson @Bertrandization @CaseyBriggs @Chrisbilbo @matt_barrie @normanswan @GregDore2 @cbaker_research @YouAreLobbyLud 'I really am not seeing a magic bullet here.'

I asked Prof Doherty about Singapore. He emphasized compliance.

I think (v broad) formula for success would be:
